Dialogue: 0,0:00:03.77,0:00:05.40,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,This way, this way!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:05.40,0:00:07.65,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,There's a huge case for you!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:07.65,0:00:10.65,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,We need your help, Detective Mouri!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.65,0:00:15.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Geez, why do I have to be dragged around by these brats this early in the morning...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.41,0:00:17.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're did accept their request, after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.66,0:00:22.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I didn't know Yōko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r} was gonna appear on TV this morning!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.66,0:00:25.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Everyone's hyped up this morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.04,0:00:26.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Totally.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.59,0:00:31.67,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Seeking comprehensive answers,\Nhe solves every mystery and code!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.67,0:00:35.22,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}A fallen victim's surprising trick in a town centre flowerbed.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.22,0:00:37.05,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}He sees the single truth for what it is,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.05,0:00:38.85,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}and looks like a kid but has the mind of an adult!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.85,0:00:42.02,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}His name? Detective Conan!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.37,0:02:34.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Beika Town Centre?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.04,0:02:40.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, it's a place which people who live locally can use to play sports and so on.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.76,0:02:44.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Either way, it's not somewhere you'd expect a case.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.97,0:02:46.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Here!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.35,0:02:52.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Isn't it awful?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.48,0:02:56.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's a mess, it looks like a cyclone blew through here!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.40,0:03:04.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The flowers and plants here are all planted and even watered by children.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.28,0:03:08.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But recently, it gets vandalised every morning!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.03,0:03:10.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It must be some bad guy!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.12,0:03:12.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Please catch him, Uncle!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.37,0:03:15.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Go and ask your mother or your teacher instead.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.83,0:03:17.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Dad!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.29,0:03:21.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So Detective Mouri won't solve it after all?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.71,0:03:25.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He even told us we could count on him when we called him earlier...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.93,0:03:27.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right, Genta{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.26,0:03:28.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.10,0:03:31.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Huh? That's weird.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.56,0:03:32.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.98,0:03:35.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The brick I made is missing.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.81,0:03:38.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was always right here before.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.98,0:03:42.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Maybe the flowerbed vandal\Naccidentally stepped on it and broke it?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.65,0:03:45.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Damn, talk about a horrible guy.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.07,0:03:48.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If Uncle won't help us, let's find the vandal ourselves!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.07,0:03:49.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Let's catch him!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.87,0:03:50.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.99,0:03:53.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You can't! You're just kids.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.08,0:03:57.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The vandal comes out at night,\Nso it'll be dangerous if there's no adults around.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.00,0:04:01.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Come on, Dad! You have to keep your promise!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.88,0:04:05.56,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}So the Great Detective finally makes his entrance.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.47,0:04:08.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Babysitting a bunch of brats...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.34,0:04:10.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, you all came?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.85,0:04:17.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She's so beautiful!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.56,0:04:21.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Good morning, Yamazaki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, Saki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.52,0:04:25.94,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Toshiko Yamazaki (43)\NTown Centre Staff Member
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.69,0:04:25.94,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,It's annoying how this gets vandalised every morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.94,0:04:29.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Miss, do you work at this centre?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.62,0:04:33.04,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Saki Okamura (24)\NTown Centre Staff Member
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.37,0:04:33.04,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Y-Yes, that's right. And you are?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.04,0:04:36.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I accepted a request to investigate the flowerbed vandal,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.66,0:04:39.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm the Great Detective Kogorō Mouri!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.79,0:04:42.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A detective?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.34,0:04:46.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, stop wasting time and help me with this.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.05,0:04:49.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,S-Sure! Excuse me.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.18,0:04:55.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Nice to see you.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.06,0:04:58.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, that's not how you use splints.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.89,0:05:02.73,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,If you amateurs try and fix it,\Nyou'll just make the flowerbed even worse.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.14,0:05:02.73,Character Card,,0,0,0,,{\fad(250,0)}Ryūnosuke Okuda (57)\NFlower Shop Owner
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.73,0:05:06.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I asked you for a delivery, not your idle comments!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.99,0:05:10.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How about you leave the repairs to a professional?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.49,0:05:11.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'll give you a good price.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.62,0:05:17.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Let's see... The saplings, fertiliser, and the charge for the repairs needed would cost...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.70,0:05:20.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I just told you I don't need your idle comments.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.00,0:05:24.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,For some reason everybody wants to extort whatever money they can.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.09,0:05:26.59,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Everybody?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.59,0:05:30.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then if I throw in some extras for free, this is the total.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.55,0:05:34.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Excuse me, Yamazaki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} already refused your offer.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.35,0:05:36.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't you butt in!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.31,0:05:38.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, what are you doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.85,0:05:39.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Shut up!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.60,0:05:42.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This land belongs to me to begin with!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.69,0:05:44.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm free to do whatever I want!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.61,0:05:47.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Young lady, are you hurt?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.07,0:05:49.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, I'm fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.44,0:05:55.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As the Great Detective Kogorō Mouri, I won't forgive you for being violent toward a beautiful lady!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.91,0:05:57.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A detective?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.92,0:06:12.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So, the vandalism occurs sometime between\Nwhen the staff leave at night, and the next morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.13,0:06:14.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When did it start?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.64,0:06:16.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Today's the third day.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.31,0:06:19.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you would forgive me, we're busy here in the morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.31,0:06:22.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Okay, no more detective games for you!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.14,0:06:27.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,By the way, do you know anyone who would\Nhold a grudge against this town centre?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.27,0:06:29.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There is one person at least.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.40,0:06:32.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, that guy, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.66,0:06:39.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You kids need to get to school!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.45,0:06:43.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The bricks for the flowerbed are made here?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.67,0:06:50.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, they all vary in size and shape because they're all baked by the children.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.97,0:06:56.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So the flowerbed vandal's trampling\Non all the children's feelings as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.18,0:06:58.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He's gonna show up again tonight, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.72,0:07:01.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If it happened three times, it'll\Nhappen a fourth time for sure!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.64,0:07:06.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Let's do night patrols with old man Mouri and catch the culprit!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.40,0:07:10.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, hey...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.44,0:07:13.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They're enthusiastic.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.53,0:07:15.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see, interesting.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.41,0:07:17.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So your family live and work at that café.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.70,0:07:20.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I often pass by that area.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.58,0:07:22.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Next time, please come in.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.62,0:07:24.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Treating you to a beer is the least I can do.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.41,0:07:28.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is that so? Then I'll come check it out tonight!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.21,0:07:29.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Huh? Tonight?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.92,0:07:32.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Geez! Don't get {\i1}too{\i0} friendly!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.34,0:07:34.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Uncle Kogorō!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.88,0:07:38.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We'd like to do night patrols to catch the culprit.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.31,0:07:40.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.10,0:07:41.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is 8 PM fine for you?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.68,0:07:44.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.39,0:07:47.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're so helpful to everyone!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.35,0:07:49.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, that's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.23,0:07:53.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Defeating the strong and helping the weak is what detectives do!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.07,0:08:01.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Okay, kids, Uncle will take you to school!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.45,0:08:04.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,See you tonight, then.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.04,0:08:06.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, right.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.00,0:08:07.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hold on, Ayumi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.13,0:08:09.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Here you go.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.92,0:08:12.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's what I promised you the other day.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.09,0:08:15.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Its flowers bloom at night.\NI took some from my garden.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.84,0:08:18.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, amazing! Thank you!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.59,0:08:21.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I have one more, so I'll give you one, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.06,0:08:23.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.06,0:08:30.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Here's your second one.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.90,0:08:33.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Thank you, Saki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-tan{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.98,0:08:35.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Welcome.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.07,0:08:37.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.07,0:08:41.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, Miss!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.62,0:08:45.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,My mother's on a trip right now, so I\Nwork here part-time, during the night.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.54,0:08:47.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's a wonderful café.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.71,0:08:50.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You said it was your home.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.04,0:08:53.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, we live on the upper floors.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.75,0:08:55.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Do you want something to drink?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.55,0:08:59.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sorry, we can't. I just came to pick up my dad.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.51,0:09:03.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Dad, you promised Ayumi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r} that you'd meet her at 8, remember?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.26,0:09:06.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Like I could leave without having tasted Saki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-tan{\r}'s beers!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.48,0:09:09.49,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Looks like there's no way he's leaving.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.44,0:09:13.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sorry. I gave him too much alcohol.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.44,0:09:15.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What a mess...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.49,0:09:21.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We're late because of you, old man!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.49,0:09:25.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's 10 PM already. The vandal might already be gone by now!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.70,0:09:28.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is the children's flowerbed okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.50,0:09:31.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The flowers!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.71,0:09:37.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What is it?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.72,0:09:46.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's that employee, Yamazaki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.18,0:09:48.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ran, call an ambulance and the police!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.77,0:09:49.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Okay!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.77,0:09:54.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Kudō{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}, look at that.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.61,0:09:59.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This petal...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.03,0:10:03.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Uncle! Somebody's running away!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.78,0:10:07.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I won't let you get away!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.17,0:10:17.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You got him!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.17,0:10:20.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's him!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.30,0:10:22.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The flower shop guy!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.94,0:10:33.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The victim was Toshiko Yamazaki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r},\Nan employee from the town centre.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.94,0:10:37.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The estimated time of death is around 8 PM.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.86,0:10:45.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There are marks all over her body from was beaten, but the direct cause of death was probably her head hitting a brick.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.37,0:10:48.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The wound on her head matches the nearby bricks.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.16,0:10:53.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The bricks are unique since they\Nare made by the children here.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.25,0:10:54.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The ones who found the corpse were...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.54,0:10:57.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I can't believe kids are out this late.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.96,0:11:00.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We were looking for the flowerbed vandal!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.05,0:11:03.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Uncle Mouri was here to watch over us.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.05,0:11:05.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right, I got it, I got it.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.35,0:11:07.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And he is...?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.72,0:11:10.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The owner of a nearby flower shop, Okuda{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.35,0:11:14.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He was hiding in the shadows when we\Ndiscovered the corpse, and tried to escape,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.23,0:11:16.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,so I caught him.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.11,0:11:21.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That man has some kind of grudge against our town centre.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.20,0:11:22.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And you are?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.24,0:11:24.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A colleague of the deceased Yamazaki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.78,0:11:32.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Until a year ago, he ran his flower shop here, but he was evicted when the town centre was built.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.54,0:11:36.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But he still loathes the centre and\Nvandalises the flowerbed every night.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.25,0:11:41.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Exactly. Since I was forced to move, business has been getting worse.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.76,0:11:44.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Of course it got on my nerves!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.13,0:11:46.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, I {\i1}was{\i} the flowerbed vandal.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.22,0:11:53.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But when I arrived today, the flowerbed was already messed up and this woman was lying there.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.77,0:11:55.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Inspector!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.73,0:12:03.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Judging from the circumstances, Yamazaki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}\Nlikely fell from the emergency stairs there.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.28,0:12:08.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes. According to forensics, there are footprints on the third floor of the stairs
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.28,0:12:11.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,which match Yamazaki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s shoes and Okuda{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s gardening boots,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.54,0:12:14.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and show what appears to have been a struggle.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.50,0:12:16.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I figured it out, Inspector!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.58,0:12:25.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Around 8 PM, Okuda{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} started arguing with Yamazaki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}\Non that landing, and she fell off during their struggle.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.76,0:12:31.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He got scared and ran away,\Nbut around 10 PM, he came back to have a look.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.31,0:12:34.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And so we spotted him while patrolling.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.94,0:12:36.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's not it!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.06,0:12:42.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Those stairs are the only place where we can smoke in\Nthis centre, so I went there this morning for a smoke.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.15,0:12:46.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She came to chase me out and\Nwe may have fought a bit, but that's all.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.82,0:12:50.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What about at 8 PM?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.66,0:12:54.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Can you tell us what were you doing and where?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.16,0:13:00.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I was delivering flowers, but it must've been some sort of prank, as I was given a fake address.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.92,0:13:03.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I was driving my truck around looking for it.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.63,0:13:06.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Was there anyone with you or anyone who could confirm your story?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.80,0:13:07.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.97,0:13:11.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see. So you don't have an alibi.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.18,0:13:13.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Please come with us to the police station for now.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.89,0:13:14.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.77,0:13:15.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.27,0:13:21.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I didn't do anything! It's gotta be a mistake!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.23,0:13:26.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Anyway, why did Yamazaki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} come here at 8 PM?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.95,0:13:28.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Umm...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.20,0:13:31.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She may have came to look for this.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.49,0:13:35.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I manage the accounting here, but recently the books and the money don't match up.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.70,0:13:38.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As if somebody'd been embezzling the money.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.29,0:13:39.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Embezzling?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.38,0:13:40.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.50,0:13:43.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was most likely Yamazaki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.30,0:13:48.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I think she realised I knew, so she came here at night to hide the evidence.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.18,0:13:51.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But I had hidden the accounting book, so she couldn't find it.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.14,0:13:57.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see! Then she met Okuda{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r},\Nand he pushed her off the emergency stairs.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.35,0:14:00.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It makes sense.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.23,0:14:03.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As expected from a Great Detective. A wonderful deduction.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.44,0:14:06.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Nah, a trivial case like this is a piece of cake to me!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.03,0:14:15.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It seems {\i1}somebody{\i0} isn't sure we caught the right suspect.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.95,0:14:17.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Look.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.25,0:14:21.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What are those lines?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.08,0:14:23.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's like a cord was dragged here.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.46,0:14:28.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yamazaki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s shoelaces must've come loose while she was fighting with someone here.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.67,0:14:30.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But that can't be!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.47,0:14:31.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.43,0:14:35.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The shoelaces on the corpse were tied up tightly.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.10,0:14:38.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Which means...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.31,0:14:42.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Inspector Takagi!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.81,0:14:45.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Were there any flower petals on the victim's clothes?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.11,0:14:48.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You mean this?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.40,0:14:54.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's no surprise, she {\i1}did{\i0} fall onto a flowerbed.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.24,0:14:56.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Give it to forensics just in case.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.08,0:14:56.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.50,0:15:05.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That petal doesn't seem to be from this flowerbed.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.96,0:15:10.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah. And it's a darker colour than when we saw it earlier.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.38,0:15:12.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Could it be?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.60,0:15:18.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Could the bag you got this morning be...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.39,0:15:20.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.60,0:15:23.27,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}I see. So, that's what happened!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.81,0:15:26.27,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}But there's no evidence.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.27,0:15:29.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But it's a good thing we caught the culprit.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.15,0:15:30.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.36,0:15:33.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Now the flowerbed won't be vandalised anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.16,0:15:34.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It ain't 'good' at all!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.95,0:15:39.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We still don't know where my brick is!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.66,0:15:44.63,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}The evidence is probably still there!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.88,0:15:56.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Destroying evidence, are we?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.22,0:16:00.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As I thought, you were the real killer.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.60,0:16:03.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You almost fooled me...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.40,0:16:10.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A beaten corpse. The bricks next to it.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.07,0:16:15.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Anyone would think Yamazaki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} died\Nfalling off those emergency stairs.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.24,0:16:21.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yamazaki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} and Okuda{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s footprints were on those stairs.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.50,0:16:27.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So nobody doubted that Okuda{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, who held a grudge against\Nthe town centre, had pushed Yamazaki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} off.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.46,0:16:34.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You tried to frame Okuda{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} as the killer, since he didn't\Nhave an alibi, but you made two small mistakes.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.97,0:16:38.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The first one was the shoelaces on the corpse's shoes.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.43,0:16:46.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,On the landing, there were marks from shoelaces being dragged on the floor, as well as Okuda{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} and Yamazaki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s footprints.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.23,0:16:52.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yamazaki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s shoelace probably came loose\Nwhile they were fighting.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.15,0:16:57.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But the corpse that fell on the\Nflowerbed had her shoelaces tied.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.45,0:17:03.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Which means Yamazaki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} didn't fall then.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.75,0:17:08.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, the flowers blooming on the counter and\Nin the garden are beautiful.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.54,0:17:12.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Since they're blooming this late at night, they must be evening primroses.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.50,0:17:19.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When evening primrose first bloom in the evening, they\Nare white, but during the night, they slowly become pink.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.26,0:17:23.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And those evening primroses were your second mistake.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.22,0:17:29.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Since evening primroses only bloom during the night, they couldn't be being grown in the children's flowerbed.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.56,0:17:34.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yet evening primrose petals were found on the corpse's back.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.99,0:17:44.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The scent of evening primrose guided me to you... the real killer.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.54,0:17:46.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right, Okamura{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.75,0:17:49.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What are you trying to say?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.29,0:17:53.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Anyone could've tied her shoelaces, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.50,0:17:56.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Evening primrose isn't exactly rare either.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.51,0:18:00.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Even the police said the killer was that flowerbed vandal.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.51,0:18:05.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, everyone knew the\Nflowerbed vandal was Okuda{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.56,0:18:07.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He had monetary problems,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.31,0:18:13.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,so he'd been vandalising this flowerbed so you'd\Npay him for new saplings and bulbs and to do repairs.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.02,0:18:17.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So you set up a plan to frame him.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.82,0:18:23.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You witnessed Yamazaki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} and Okuda{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} fighting on the stair landing this morning
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.08,0:18:26.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and decided to use that spot as the crime scene.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.83,0:18:33.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, to make sure he had no alibi, you ordered him to make a delivery at 8 PM, to a fake address.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.84,0:18:35.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What are you saying?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.59,0:18:38.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Didn't Yamazaki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} die at 8 PM?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.67,0:18:45.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I was working at the café from 7:00\Nto 9:30 and never went outside.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.56,0:18:48.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And you should know, you were with me the whole time!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.68,0:18:52.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,True, the town centre is more than 5 km from this café.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.90,0:18:56.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It'd take 10 minutes just to travel there and back by car.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.99,0:19:02.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's an interesting theory, but you\Nforgot the most important part.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.95,0:19:08.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I couldn't have been there when Yamazaki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} fell.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.00,0:19:10.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The key was the bricks.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.37,0:19:14.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You took advantage of the flowerbed\Nvandalism that started three days ago,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.58,0:19:23.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and knowing nobody would notice, started stealing bricks from the flowerbed, and lined them up in the café garden.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.89,0:19:33.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yamazaki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} wasn't killed at the town\Ncentre —\hshe was killed in this garden!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.52,0:19:35.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So your alibi is no longer valid.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.90,0:19:40.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In other words, you used a trick to conceal the crime scene.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.15,0:19:44.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You called Yamazaki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} here before opening the shop,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.95,0:19:47.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,took her upstairs, and drugged her to make her fall asleep,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.91,0:19:54.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,then you worked at the café's ground floor from 7:00 to 9:30, establishing your alibi.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.21,0:19:59.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,While you were working, you left the counter to go to the toilet for about 5 minutes at around 8:00.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.76,0:20:04.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You tied Yamazaki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s shoelace while she was sleeping,{mistimed, should end 1.5s earlier at scene change}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.26,0:20:08.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and threw her out of the 3rd floor window and onto the bricks placed in the garden to kill her.{mistimed, should start 1.5s earlier at scene change}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.72,0:20:13.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's when the evening primrose petals got on her clothes.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.52,0:20:22.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Afterwards, you put her corpse in your car boot, and after closing the café, you moved her to the town centre.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.24,0:20:29.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This morning, you heard me and Ayumi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r} talking, and knew we intended to patrol tonight.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.53,0:20:37.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You went ahead of us to make sure we'd find the corpse, which would confirm your alibi.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.58,0:20:41.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Everything you've been saying is nothing but fantasy!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.92,0:20:44.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Do you have any proof that I killed her?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.93,0:20:49.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Some of the bricks you stole from the centre should still be in your garden.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.18,0:20:50.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, Conan!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.76,0:20:51.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.64,0:20:58.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah! There's lots of bricks here, just like Uncle said!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.61,0:21:07.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Since you were summoned for your testimony just after\Nmoving the corpse, you didn't have time to clean up your garden.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.66,0:21:15.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,An investigation of these bricks should reveal traces proving Yamazaki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was killed here.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.17,0:21:19.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Now, this is just conjecture, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.88,0:21:23.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You were the one who was embezzling the centre's money, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.38,0:21:27.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And Yamazaki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} became a danger when she started investigating...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.43,0:21:31.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're right. I have debt issues...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.85,0:21:35.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Even though I was working the night shift at my mother's café, it still wasn't enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.73,0:21:38.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So I took money from the centre.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.15,0:21:44.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When Yamazaki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} noticed,\Nshe threatened to fire me.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.40,0:21:49.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's why... That's why I had to...!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:15.40,0:23:19.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm so glad my brick's safe.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:19.02,0:23:21.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,To be made by Kojima{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:21.88,0:23:24.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Let me see, what is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:24.02,0:23:27.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Here! Ta-da!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:27.84,0:23:29.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't tell me that's...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:29.80,0:23:31.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You figured it out?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:31.53,0:23:34.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, it's an eel lunch!
